<div id="Idea_3385"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3385-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3385">FAR Definition of 'DATA' Includes Software - Encourage Re-use - Save $s&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5758-4049">Peter Gallagher</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">5 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Leverage the federal definition of “data” - The Federal IT industry will be radically changed if all government-funded data (work products like software code, models, and other artifacts) is transparent and accessible. The publishing of all types of data, especially software code and business process models, by Federal contractors should be encouraged. One way to do this is to value re-use strategies when evaluationg procurements. Just as we value past performance we should value re-use strategies, including the commercial publishing of govermnment funded IT activities as open source software. This commercial approach will stimulate a whole new range of shared solutions and encourage better integration of services across the government.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3385" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3385', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=3385')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3385"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=far">far</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=open source">open source</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=re-use">re-use</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3385"></div>
