<div id="Idea_3354"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3354-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3354">Require ALL Government contracts to be posted online in full text&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5838-4049">Rich Wilkinson</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">5 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Every document by which the Federal Government acquires goods or services should be accessible by any citizen. The argument that public contracts contain proprietary information is simply false. I have seen FOIA requests for contracts redacted to conceal the price(s) of the (T&M) labor rates. The price the Government pays for goods and services should be public knowledge. If a contractor is unwilling to disclose the prices they charge, they should simply find another market in which to sell.</div>
